本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:陳鴻斌研究生(外文):Hung-Pin Chen論文名稱:行動醫療與情境感知應用研究論文名稱(外文):行動醫療與情境感知應用研究指導教授:鄭進興指導教授(外文):Jinn-Shing Cheng學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立高雄第一科技大學系所名稱:資訊管理研究所學門:電算機學門學類:電算機一般學類論文出版年:2016畢業學年度:104語文別:中文論文頁數:103中文關鍵詞:情境感知的應用、行動醫療、室內定位、物聯網、醫療資訊系統外文關鍵詞:Indoor Positioning、Context-aware Applications、IOT(Internet Of Things)、Health Information Systems(HIS)、Mobile Medical Applications相關次數:

被引用:0點閱:56評分:下載:0書目收藏:1



為達到病人在醫療的過程中能夠更加人性化與自動化，訊息能更加透通，以及有效利用時間而降低每次的醫療等待時間，本研究運用物聯網(IOT)概念、室內定位以及行動裝置與情境感知的應用，系統可以依照病人所在的位置與環境去預測患者的需求並主動提供患者所需要的服務建議，再結合醫療系統的應用，主動偵測病人狀況及主動提醒病人下一步流程，並在行動裝置上提供醫療資訊與進階的訊息，提高醫療資訊的透明度及部份解決訊息不對稱的問題。不但可減少患者等待時間且可以減少病人的壓力與不確定的情緒，另一方面則可降低醫療人員的工作負擔以及工作被打斷的恢復成本，進而達到藉由系統提高醫療透明，有效運用時間、更佳的人性化與提高“醫病”之間的關係與滿意度，建構以患者為中心的思考，以病人服務為目標的行動醫療感知系統。

The goal of this research is to make the medical process more humanized and automatic, exchange the information smoother, use the time more efficiently, and reduce the time of waiting. To accomplish that, we use the concept of “Internet of Things” (IOT), indoor positioning, and the application of mobile devices with context-aware to allow the system to predict the need of patients based on the location or the environment of them, and to provide the service advices of their needs. Combined with the application of the health care system, it can detect the status of the patient and remind the patient about the following actions proactively. The medical information and the advanced message will be provided on the mobile devices which can improve the transparency of medical information and solve some of the problems toward asymmetric message. With this, we can not only prevent the patient from waiting and reduce their stress and the uncertain emotion, but also lower the loading of care providers and the chance of being interrupted from their ongoing works. Therefore, we can improve the transparency of medical information, achieve the efficiency of time, humanize the medical process to enhance the relation and satisfaction between patients and care providers, and construct a mobile medical cognitive system with the patient-centered concept and patient service as the target.

